\begin_layout Solution
For the first part,
 we need to show that the axioms of 
\begin_inset Formula $\ZF$
\end_inset

 hold of 
\begin_inset Formula $\class M$
\end_inset

.
 Most of them follow very directly.
 For example,
 for union:
 If 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in\class M$
\end_inset

,
 then 
\begin_inset Formula $\cup x\subseteq\class M$
\end_inset

 by transitivity,
 then we pick 
\begin_inset Formula $y\supseteq\cup x$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\class M$
\end_inset

 and use comprehension to cut 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 down to the set of its elements that are in some element of 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 This gives you 
\begin_inset Formula $\cup x\in\class M$
\end_inset

.
 Other axioms that follow this pattern:
 Powerset (need to use 
\begin_inset Formula $\powerset(x)\cap\class M\subseteq\class M$
\end_inset

 instead),
 pairing,
 and infinity (use 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega$
\end_inset

 and the absolute formula 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

is a finite ordinal
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

).
 Since extensionality and foundation are direct in any transitive class,
 it suffices to verify the axiom schema of replacement.
 It's like the other axioms,
 but I'll do it in more detail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution
Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi(x,y,\vec{p})$
\end_inset

 be a class function on 
\begin_inset Formula $X\in\class M$
\end_inset

 from the perspective of 
\begin_inset Formula $\class M$
\end_inset

.
 Then,
 it induces a class function on 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 from the perspective of ambient space via 
\begin_inset Formula $\varphi^{\class M}(x,y,\vec{p})\land y\in\class M$
\end_inset

.
 Apply replacement (on ambient space) to get the set 
\begin_inset Formula $Y=\{y\in\class M\mid\exists_{x\in X}\varphi^{\class M}(x,y,\vec{p})\}$
\end_inset

,
 which is a subset of 
\begin_inset Formula $\class M$
\end_inset

,
 and so is contained in some 
\begin_inset Formula $Z\in\class M$
\end_inset

.
 Applying comprehension on 
\begin_inset Formula $Z$
\end_inset

 (from the perspective of 
\begin_inset Formula $\class M$
\end_inset

) with the formula 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi(y,\vec{p})\equiv\exists_{x\in X}\varphi(x,y,\vec{p})$
\end_inset

,
 we recover exactly 
\begin_inset Formula $Y\in\class M$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

