\begin_inset Formula $\Phi(x,y)$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\class{Ord}\cup T\cup\{T\}\right)^{<\omega}$
\end_inset

.
 This formula goes something along the lines of:
 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 is the 
\begin_inset Formula $(y_{0},\dots,y_{\mathrm{length}(y)-2})$
\end_inset

-th section of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Enod}(y_{\mathrm{length}(y)-1})$
\end_inset

 (where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathrm{Enod}$
\end_inset

